                  A bad smell from your washing machine can be caused by mold or
                  mildew buildup. Regularly running a cleaning cycle with a
                  washing machine cleaner can help eliminate odors. Leaving the
                  washer lid open after each use allows the machine to dry out,
                  preventing mold growth. Check the detergent drawer and seals
                  for any trapped debris and clean them thoroughly. Regular
                  maintenance and cleaning can keep your washer smelling fresh.
                  If the smell persists, deeper cleaning or professional help
                  might be required.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="content__page-desc">
                <h3>Washer Not Starting:</h3>
