                  signs of wear or damage to the lock mechanism. If the door
                  doesn’t close tight, it might need an adjustment. Regularly
                  cleaning the door seal can also help maintain the lock’s
                  efficiency. Always ensure the door is properly closed before
                  starting a cycle to avoid interruptions.
                </p>
              </div>
